Neil MacGregor has been at the helm of the British Museum since 2002 . 
  He said it was 'a difficult thing' to leave and will retire at the end of the year . 
  The 68-year-old previously ran the National Gallery and Radio 4 series A History Of The World In 100 Objects . 
  He has been in charge of the museum since 2002 and said it is 'the greatest privilege of his professional life'